slope
terrain slope refers to the measurement of steepness or incline at any given point on the land surface.
It is an essential part of terrain analysis. A slope is represented as an angle in degrees or as a percentage.
Slope Calculation in Degrees (0-90): Slope is expressed as the angle between a horizontal plane and a terrain surface. A 0° slope denotes a flat terrain whereas, a 90° slope represents a vertical incline.
