aspect
Aspect, in the context of geographical and environmental concepts, refers to the direction that a slope faces in relation to the cardinal points (north, south, east, west).
Aspect helps in determining the microclimate of an area as it influences the amount of sunlight that particular area happens to receive throughout the day.
South-facing slopes receive more sunlight as compared to the north-facing slopes.
The method of calculating aspects involves the analysis of DEMs and other topographic data. The aspect is shown in the data as an angle ranging from 0 to 360 degrees.
Allow us to share what the values correspond to:  0° corresponds to the north, 90° corresponds to the east, 180° corresponds to the south and 270° corresponds to the west. 
